liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Three red lights spell the end for Shardul Thakur, a perfect off spinner's wicket for Nathan Lyon. A bit of drift away from the batter and plenty of spin back into him. Thakur was absolutely plumb in front and departs without troubling the scorers. Three to go.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: OUT! Thakur is gone for a duck, Lyon strikes!

children.content: Three red lights spell the end for Shardul Thakur, a perfect off spinner's wicket for Nathan Lyon. A bit of drift away from the batter and plenty of spin back into him. Thakur was absolutely plumb in front and departs without troubling the scorers.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: It's come from nowhere, such a loose shot from Rahane after a morning of composure. It wasn't full enough to drive, but the width sucked Rahane in and brought about a poor wafting drive. Another nick, another Carey catch, another step closer for Australia.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: GOT HIM! Starc strikes and Rahane is gone!

children.content: It's come from nowhere, such a loose shot from Rahane after a morning of composure. It wasn't full enough to drive, but the width sucked Rahane in and brought about a poor wafting drive. Another nick, another Carey catch, another step closer for Australia.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Stop what you're doing, Scott Boland is doing it again! Around the wicket to the left-hander, Boland is full and tempting and seaming away, catching a healthy edge through to Alex Carey. He has been tight and probing all morning, but in the space of three balls has blown this match wide open.
